IPL is one of my favorite medical grade facials both for myself and my patients. It evens out the complexion beautifully and helps remove brown and red spots from sun damage and the aging process. It also treats broken blood vessels as well as redness and rosacea. It can be done anywhere on the body (face, neck, chest, arms, etc.) and is safe and effective for light to medium skin tones. It is quick, relatively comfortable and you can return to work and your life immediately after the treatment (with all of the sun protection of course).

Chemical peels are acids used to exfoliate the very top layer of our skin. They can be useful for treating acne, hyperpigmentation, melasma, and skin texture. During the procedure we prep the skin by dermaplaning and cleansing to ensure even penetration of the solution, and apply several layers of the peel to the area. Peels can vary in their downtime but more superficial peels usually get dry and flakey for a few days and in about a week your skin is healed and glowing!

Microneedling is one of my favorite medical grade facials. At Grace, we use the SkinPen because it is the first FDA-cleared microneedling device and we strive to offer the safest and most effective treatments. The appointment typically takes around 30 minutes, and is well tolerated with just a few days of downtime. Because its designed to work without using heat or chemicals it is safe to use year round and on all skin tones. We recommend 3-4 treatments done about 4-6 weeks apart.
